foreignText: Quis tam  Perditus, ut dubitet Senecam praeferre Neroni?
Nemo petit, modicis quae mittebantur amicis   A Seneca; quae Piso bonus, quae Cotta solebat   Largiri: namque & titulis, & fascibus olim   Major habebatur donandi gloria.
citations: Hesitating whether he should make a bench or a Priapus. . . . So I am a God!

Those who have read it have been able to see in general that the Author has not proposed there any particular plan, for the purpose of treating his material methodically; because it is a Letter and not a Treatise.
